<p>Reports managed beans with public instance fields that are not in the default <code>@Dependent</code> scope.
  According to the CDI specification, contextual scopes
  (<code>@RequestScoped</code>, <code>@ApplicationScoped</code>, <code>@SessionScoped</code>, and <code>ConversationScoped</code>)
  are not allowed for managed beans with public instance fields.
</p>
<p><b>Example:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="java">
  @ApplicationScoped // Warning: Bean with non-default scope must not have public fields
  class Car {
    public String engine;
  }
</code></pre>
